//   {"id":890,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 14: Introduction to acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"When zinc powder is added to dilute hydrochloric acid, colourless gas bubbles evolve. Which of the following is the observable change at the end when excess ammonia solution is added to the resultant mixture?","points":5,"options":["A brown gas evolves.","A white precipitate forms.","A grey solid appears."," There is no observable change."],"answerLetter":"D"},
//   {"id":891,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 14: Introduction to acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"The following tests were carried out to identify an unknown compound X.\n\nTest\tResults\n(1) Add dilute hydrochloric acid to the compound\tA colourless gas evolves. The gas evolved can turn limewater milky.\n(2) Heat the compound with sodium hydroxide solution\tA colourless gas evolves. The gas evolved can turn moist red litmus paper blue.\n\nWhich of the following compounds would solid X be?","points":5,"options":["Ammonium sulphate","Ammonium carbonate","Copper(II) sulphate"," Copper(II) carbonate"],"answerLetter":"B"},
//   {"id":892,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 14: Introduction to acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Solid X is soluble in cold water. When excess ammonia solution is added to the solution of X, a precipitate first forms and then dissolve When X is mixed with sodium chloride solution, a precipitate forms. Which of the following could X be?","points":5,"options":["Lead(II) nitrate","Zinc bromide","Silver nitrate"," Copper(II) sulphate"],"answerLetter":"C"},
//   {"id":893,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 14: Introduction to acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"A mixture of solution X and solution Y is a clear colourless solution. When the mixture is heated with excess NaOH(aq), a pungent gas evolves and a white precipitate forms. Which of the following combinations of X and Y is correct?\n\nSolution X\tSolution Y\n(NH4)2SO4(aq)\tCaCl2(aq)\n(NH4)2SO4(aq)\tKCl(aq)\nNH4Cl(aq)\tMgSO4(aq)\n NH4Cl(aq)\tPb(NO3)2(aq)","points":5,"options":["(NH4)2SO4(aq) and CaCl2(aq)","(NH4)2SO4(aq) and KCl(aq)","NH4Cl(aq) and MgSO4(aq)"," NH4Cl(aq) and Pb(NO3)2(aq)"],"answerLetter":"C"},
