//   {"id":990,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following methods can be used to distinguish between 0.5 M NH3(aq) and 0.5 M NaOH(aq)?\n(1) Add calcium nitrate solution to each solution.\n(2) Compare the electrical conductivities of the two solutions.\n(3) Perform flame test.","points":5,"options":["A. (1) and (2) only","B. (1) and (3) only","C. (2) and (3) only","D. (1), (2) and (3)"],"answerLetter":"D"},
//   {"id":991,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements concerning NH3(aq) and NaOH(aq) is correct?","points":5,"options":["A. The electrical conductivity of 0.5 M NH3(aq) is higher than that of 0.5 M NaOH(aq).","B. NaOH is a weaker alkali than NH3.","C. Both excess NH3(aq) and excess NaOH(aq) react with ZnCl2(aq) to give a clear solution.","D. Both 100 cm^3 of 0.1 M NH3(aq) and 100 cm^3 of 0.1 M NaOH(aq) react with 100 cm^3 of 0.1 M HCl(aq) to give out the same amount of heat."],"answerLetter":"C"},
//   {"id":992,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements about a concentrated acid is correct?","points":5,"options":["A. It reacts with copper.","B. It does not react with copper(II) oxide.","C. It is an acid that completely ionizes in water.","D. It must contain hydrogen ions when dissolved in water."],"answerLetter":"D"},
//   {"id":993,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements about a dilute solution of strong acid is correct?","points":5,"options":["A. It is a strong electrolyte.","B. It has a pH value of 1.","C. It is bitter in taste.","D. It reacts with all metals."],"answerLetter":"A"},
//   {"id":994,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Sulphuric acid is a stronger acid than ethanoic acid because\n(1) sulphuric acid is a dibasic acid while ethanoic acid is a monobasic acid.\n(2) sulphuric acid highly ionizes in water while ethanoic acid only slightly ionizes in water.\n(3) the concentration of hydrogen ions in 1.0 M sulphuric acid is higher than that in 1.0 M ethanoic acid.","points":5,"options":["A. (1) only","B. (2) only","C. (1) and (3) only","D. (2) and (3) only"],"answerLetter":"B"},
//   {"id":995,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements about ammonia solution is correct?","points":5,"options":["A. Concentrated ammonia solution is a strong alkali.","B. Dilute ammonia solution contains NH4+(aq), H+(aq), OH−(aq) and NH3(aq).","C. 1 M ammonia solution has the same pH value as 1 M sodium hydroxide solution.","D. When ammonia solution is added to iron(II) nitrate solution, a brown precipitate forms."],"answerLetter":"B"},
//   {"id":996,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Assertion: HCl(aq) is a stronger acid than CH3COOH(aq).\nReason: HCl completely ionizes when it dissolves in water.","points":5,"options":["A. Both statements are true and the 2nd statement is a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","B. Both statements are true but the 2nd statement is NOT a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","C. The 1st statement is false but the 2nd statement is true.","D. Both statements are false."],"answerLetter":"A"},
//   {"id":997,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Assertion: Ammonia is a weak alkali.\nReason: Ammonia is a colourless gas.","points":5,"options":["A. Both statements are true and the 2nd statement is a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","B. Both statements are true but the 2nd statement is NOT a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","C. The 1st statement is false but the 2nd statement is true.","D. Both statements are false."],"answerLetter":"B"},
//   {"id":998,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 17: Strength of acids and alkalis","type":"choice","text":"Assertion: Ammonia gas can turn dry red litmus paper blue.\nReason: Ammonia is a weak base.","points":5,"options":["A. Both statements are true and the 2nd statement is a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","B. Both statements are true but the 2nd statement is NOT a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","C. The 1st statement is false but the 2nd statement is true.","D. Both statements are false."],"answerLetter":"C"},
