//   {"id":1015,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 18: Salts and neutralization","type":"choice","text":"10 cm^3 of 1 M potassium hydroxide solution is added to 10 cm^3 of acid X and 10 cm^3 of acid Y respectively. Which of the following combinations of acids X and Y gives approximately the same temperature change of the reaction mixture?\n\nX\tY\nA. 1 M H2SO4\t2 M HCl\nB. 2 M H2SO4\t1 M HCl\nC. 1 M H2SO4\t2 M CH3COOH\nD. 1 M HNO3\t2 M HCl","points":5,"options":["A. 1 M H2SO4 and 2 M HCl","B. 2 M H2SO4 and 1 M HCl","C. 1 M H2SO4 and 2 M CH3COOH","D. 1 M HNO3 and 2 M HCl"],"answerLetter":"A"},
