//   {"id":1042,"subject":"化學","topic":"Chapter 18: Salts and neutralization","type":"choice","text":"The table below shows the observations of the chemical tests of three ionic compounds.\nCompound QT: Adding barium chloride solution: A white precipitate forms. Adding dilute hydrochloric acid: No observable change. Flame test: A lilac flame is produced.\nCompound XZ: Adding barium chloride solution: A colourless solution forms. Adding dilute hydrochloric acid: Colourless gas bubbles evolve. Flame test: A golden yellow flame is produced.\nCompound X2T: Adding barium chloride solution: A white precipitate forms. Adding dilute hydrochloric acid: No observable change. Flame test: A golden yellow flame is produced.\nWhich of the following combinations of ions involved is correct?\n\nX\tQ\tT\tZ\nA. Calcium ion\tSodium ion\tCarbonate ion\tSulphate ion\nB. Sodium ion\tPotassium ion\tCarbonate ion\tHydrogencarbonate ion\nC. Potassium ion\tSodium ion\tSulphate ion\tCarbonate ion\nD. Sodium ion\tPotassium ion\tSulphate ion\tHydrogencarbonate ion","points":5,"options":["A. X=Calcium ion, Q=Sodium ion, T=Carbonate ion, Z=Sulphate ion","B. X=Sodium ion, Q=Potassium ion, T=Carbonate ion, Z=Hydrogencarbonate ion","C. X=Potassium ion, Q=Sodium ion, T=Sulphate ion, Z=Carbonate ion","D. X=Sodium ion, Q=Potassium ion, T=Sulphate ion, Z=Hydrogencarbonate ion"],"answerLetter":"D"},
