//   {"id":1153,"subject":"化學","topic":"2A: Acids and Bases","type":"choice","text":"Assertion: To completely neutralise 1 mole of HCl(aq), the number of moles of NH₃(aq) needed is more than the number of moles of KOH(aq) needed.\nReason: NH₃(aq) is a weaker alkali than KOH(aq).","points":5,"options":["Both statements are true and the 2nd statement is a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","Both statements are true but the 2nd statement is NOT a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","The 1st statement is false but the 2nd statement is true.","Both statements are false."],"answerLetter":"C"},

        
// {"id":1155,"subject":"化學","topic":"1. Planet Earth","type":"choice","text":"SP Q3 Which of the following correctly describes the sequence of procedures to separate sand, salt and water from a mixture of sand and salt solution?","points":5,"options":["filtration, evaporation","filtration, distillation","crystallisation, filtration","crystallisation, filtration, distillation"],"answerLetter":"B"},
// {"id":1156,"subject":"化學","topic":"1. Planet Earth","type":"choice","text":"A scientist extracted a sample of 'nitrogen' from air by removing the oxygen and carbon dioxide. The scientist then compared the mass of a known volume of the 'nitrogen' sample (m1) with that of the same volume of pure nitrogen (m2) under the same set of conditions. The experiment was repeated a number of times. It was found that m1 was consistently greater than m2. Which of the following gases is likely to be present in the 'nitrogen' obtained to account for the result that m1 is greater than m2?","points":5,"options":["neon","argon","methane","water vapour"],"answerLetter":"B"},
