// {"id":1170,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements about silicon dioxide is correct?","points":5,"options":["It consists of discrete molecules.","It melts upon heating in a test tube.","It is ductile.","It is a poor conductor of electricity."],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1171,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements best describes metallic bonding?","points":5,"options":["It is an attractive force between ions.","It is an attractive force between polar chemical species.","It is an attractive force between atomic nuclei and bond-pair electrons.","It is an attractive force between cations and delocalised electrons."],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1172,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Barium (Ba) is an element in Group II of the Periodic Table. Which of the following is/are the expected observation(s) when a small piece of barium is added to a trough of water containing a few drops of phenolphthalein? (1) A colourless gas is liberated. (2) The piece of barium floats on the water surface. (3) The resulting solution in the trough is colourless.","points":5,"options":["(1) only","(2) only","(1) and (3) only","(2) and (3) only"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1173,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Silicon and carbon react to form silicon carbide. The crystal structure of silicon carbide is similar to that of diamond. Silicon carbide is very hard because","points":5,"options":["it has a high melting point.","silicon atoms and carbon atoms form triple bonds.","it has a giant network structure with strong covalent bonds.","both silicon and carbon atoms have four outermost shell electrons."],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1174,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements concerning an 131I atom and a 131Xe atom is / are correct? (1) They have the same number of protons. (2) They have different numbers of neutrons. (3) They have different numbers of outermost shell electrons.","points":5,"options":["(1) only","(2) only","(1) and (3) only","(2) and (3) only"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1175,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Suppose that element X has only two isotopes, 63X and 65X. The graph below shows the relative abundance of the two isotopes: (缺少圖片，文件名: image[[161, 107, 464, 341]]) Which of the following is the relative atomic mass of X?","points":5,"options":["63.3","63.5","63.6","64.0"],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1176,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Scadium (Sc) is a metal. Scadium, in its compounds, exhibits only one oxidation number. The chemical formula of scandium nitrate is Sc(NO3)3. Which of the following is most likely to be the chemical formula of scandium phosphate?","points":5,"options":["Sc2(PO4)3","ScPO4","Sc(PO4)2","Sc(PO4)3"],"answerLetter":"B"},
// {"id":1177,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Both radium (Ra) and calcium (Ca) belong to the same group of the Periodic Table. Which of the following statements is INCORRECT?","points":5,"options":["Radium is a good conductor of electricity in the solid state.","Radium atoms readily donate electrons to form Ra2+ ions.","Both radium and calcium become tarnished after exposed to air for some time.","Radium is less reactive than calcium."],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1178,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following atoms has the smallest number of neutrons?","points":5,"options":["63Cu","59Co","58Ni","57Fe"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1179,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following compounds has a giant ionic structure?","points":5,"options":["N2O4","HNO3","NCl3","NH4NO3"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1180,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Element Q belongs to Group II of the Periodic Table. It combines with element R to give an ionic compound with chemical formula Q3R2. Which group of the Periodic Table does R belong to?","points":5,"options":["Group III","Group V","Group VI","Group VII"],"answerLetter":"B"},
// {"id":1181,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements concerning 'atom' is correct?","points":5,"options":["All atoms do not carry net charges.","Mass is evenly distributed within an atom.","All atoms consist of protons, neutrons and electrons.","For all elements, atoms of the same element have the same mass number."],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1182,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following is the electron diagram (only electrons in the outermost shells are shown) of lithium sulphide? (缺少圖片，文件名: 圖表)","points":5,"options":["A","B","C","D"],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1183,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Consider the following information concerning metal Y: (1) Y reacts vigorously with water. (2) Y forms an oxide with chemical formula Y2O. (3) An atom of Y has five occupied electron shells. Y may be","points":5,"options":["silver (Ag).","caesium (Cs).","strontium (Sr).","rubidium (Rb)."],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1184,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Pb is an element in Group IV of the Periodic Table and can form Pb2+ ion. Which of the following statements are correct? (1) The change from Pb2+ ion to Pb atom is a reduction. (2) Both Pb atom and Pb2+ ion have the same number of protons. (3) Both Pb atom and Pb2+ ion have the same number.","points":5,"options":["(1) and (2) only","(1) and (3) only","(2) and (3) only","(1), (2) and (3)"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1185,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Elements X and Y form an ionic compound with chemical formula X2Y. If the ion of X and the ion of Y have the same electronic arrangement, which of the following may this compound be?","points":5,"options":["lithium oxide.","aluminium oxide","potassium sulphide","magnesium chloride"],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1186,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements concerning helium is / are correct? (1) Helium is chemically inert. (2) Helium exists as diatomic molecules. (3) The outermost electron shell of a helium atom has an octet structure.","points":5,"options":["(1) only","(2) only","(1) and (3) only","(2) and (3) only"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1187,"subject":"化學","topic":"2. Microscopic World I","type":"choice","text":"Quartz (SiO2) is harder than dry ice (CO2) because","points":5,"options":["the atomic size of silicon is larger than that of carbon.","a silicon atom has more electrons than a carbon atom has.","quartz has a giant network structure, but dry ice consists of discrete molecules.","the silicon-oxygen bond in quartz is strong, but the carbon-oxygen bond in dry ice is weak."],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1188,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"SP Q5 If the iron nail rusts, what would the colour of the rust indicator be around the nail?","points":5,"options":["yellow","brown","red","blue"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1189,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"SP Q6 In which of the dishes would the iron nail rust?","points":5,"options":["dish 1 only","dish 2 only","dish 1 and dish 3 only","dish 2 and dish 4 only"],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1190,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"SP Q15 Which of the following samples of gases contains the smallest number of molecules? (Relative atomic masses: H = 1.0 C = 12.0 N = 14.0 O = 16.0 S = 32.1)","points":5,"options":["10g of NO2","10g of CO2","10g of H2S","10g of C2H4"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1191,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"X, Y and Z are three different metals. When these metals are placed separately into an aqueous solution of tin(II) nitrate, a spongy layer of tin is formed only on X. When each of the oxides of these metals is heated strongly, only the oxide of Y gives a metallic lustre. Which of the following represents the arrangement of these metals in decreasing order of reactivity?","points":5,"options":["X > Y > Z","X > Z > Y","Y > X > Z","Z > X > Y"],"answerLetter":"B"},
// {"id":1192,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Consider the following chemical equation: pSO2(aq) + qCe4+(aq) + rH2O(l) -> pSO42-(aq) + qCe3+(aq) + 2rH+(aq) (Ce is the chemical symbol for cerium.) Which of the following combinations is correct?","points":5,"options":["p=1 q=1 r=1","p=1 q=1 r=2","p=1 q=2 r=2","p=2 q=1 r=2"],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1193,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"In an oxide of metal M, the mass percentage of M is 55.0%. What is the chemical formula of this oxide? (Relative atomic masses: O = 16.0 M = 39.1)","points":5,"options":["MO2","M2O","M2O2","M2O3"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1194,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following statements concerning an aluminium ore consisting mainly of Al2O3 is correct? (Relative atomic masses: O = 16.0 Al = 27.0)","points":5,"options":["Carbon can be used to extract aluminium from this ore.","The abundance of this ore in the earth crust is very low.","This ore contains more than 55% of aluminium by mass.","Aluminium can be extracted from this ore due to the advancement of technology in applying electricity."],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1195,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"The tendency of being reduced of six ionic species increases in the order as shown below: Ba2+(aq) < Na+(aq) < Mg2+(aq) < H+(aq) < Cu2+(aq) < Hg2+(aq). Which of the following statements is correct?","points":5,"options":["Ba(s) does NOT react with H+(aq).","Na(s) has a stronger reducing power than Hg(l).","Hg2+(aq) is the weakest oxidizing agent among the six species.","Displacement reaction occurs when Cu(s) is immersed in MgSO4(aq)."],"answerLetter":"B"},
// {"id":1196,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following combinations is / are correct? Object: aluminium window frames - Corresponding corrosion prevention method / principle: cathodic protection; galvanized iron buckets - sacrificial protection; tin-plated iron cans - alloying","points":5,"options":["(1) only","(2) only","(1) and (3) only","(2) and (3) only"],"answerLetter":"B"},
// {"id":1197,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"1st statement: When iron and copper are separately immersed in hexane completely, iron corrodes faster than copper. 2nd statement: Iron can be oxidised more readily than copper.","points":5,"options":["Both statements are true and the 2nd statement is a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","Both statements are true but the 2nd statement is NOT a correct explanation of the 1st statement.","The 1st statement is false but the 2nd statement is true.","Both statements are false."],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1198,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following methods can be used to obtain magnesium from magnesium compounds?","points":5,"options":["electrolysis of a molten magnesium compound","electrolysis of an aqueous solution of a magnesium compound","heating magnesium oxide with carbon","heating magnesium oxide strongly"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1199,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Both the frame and gear system of a bicycle are made of steel. Which of the following combinations can be used to prevent these parts of the bicycle from rusting? Frame: painting; Gear system: greasing","points":5,"options":["painting / greasing","painting / galvanising","tin-plating / greasing","tin-plating / galvanising"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1200,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Titanium (Ti) is a metal. 2.66 g of a sample of titanium powder is heated in excess oxygen until the metal is completely oxidised. The mass of the oxide formed is 4.44 g. Which of the following is the empirical formula of the oxide formed? (Relative atomic masses: O = 16.0 Ti = 47.9)","points":5,"options":["TiO","Ti2O3","Ti3O4","TiO2"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1201,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"The diagram below shows three iron nails of the same size and shape each immersed in a liquid. (缺少圖片，文件名: image[[139, 557, 890, 695]]) Which of the following arrangements represents the ascending order of rate of corrosion of the iron nails?","points":5,"options":["Z < Y < X","Y < Z < X","Z < X < Y","X < Z < Y"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1202,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Refer to the following chemical equation: Fe2O3(s) + 3CO(g) -> 2Fe(s) + 3CO2(g). N moles of Fe2O3 are allowed to react with 2N moles of CO under suitable conditions until the reaction stops. How many moles of Fe are formed?","points":5,"options":["N","2N","2/3 N","4/3 N"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1203,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Hydrated salt X·nH2O contains 51.16% of water by mass. Given that the molar mass of X is 120.3 g, what is n? (Relative atomic masses: H = 1.0 O = 16.0)","points":5,"options":["2","5","7","10"],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1204,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"As shown in the diagram below, the glowing splint relights when solid Z is heated. (缺少圖片，文件名: image[[319, 579, 718, 702]]) Which of the following chemicals may Z be?","points":5,"options":["HgO","Al2O3","CaCO3","MgCO3"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1205,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"In an experiment, a small piece of potassium is added to a trough of water containing phenolphthalein. Which of the following statements concerning the experiment are correct? (1) An exothermic reaction occurs. (2) A colourless solution is formed. (3) The metal burns with a lilac flame.","points":5,"options":["(1) and (2) only","(1) and (3) only","(2) and (3) only","(1), (2) and (3)"],"answerLetter":"B"},
// {"id":1206,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"The set-up of an experiment is shown below. At room temperature, the system initially contains 40 cm3 of N2(g), 25 cm3 of O2(g) and 10 cm3 of He(g). (缺少圖片，文件名: image[[120, 366, 918, 464]]) The plungers of the gas syringes are moved to and fro until there is no further change in the system. The system is then allowed to cool to room temperature. Which of the following statements concerning the experiment are correct? (1) Some copper powder would change to a black substance. (2) The total volume of the gases in the system would decrease by 25 cm3. (3) The same change in total volume of the gases would be observed if excess copper powder is replaced with excess iron powder.","points":5,"options":["(1) and (2) only","(1) and (3) only","(2) and (3) only","(1), (2) and (3)"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1207,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following processes would NOT give oxygen?","points":5,"options":["heating mercury(II) oxide strongly","electrolysis of dilute sulphuric acid","fractional distillation of liquefied air","passing steam over heated magnesium"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1208,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following salts CANNOT be prepared from the reaction of a metal with a dilute acid?","points":5,"options":["zinc sulphate","iron(II) chloride","calcium chloride","copper(II) sulphate"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1209,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"A gel containing NaCl(aq), K3Fe(CN)6(aq) and phenolphthalein is yellow in colour. An iron nail is put into the gel and corrodes after a period of time. Which of the following colours would NOT be observed in the gel after the iron nail corrodes?","points":5,"options":["blue","pink","grey","yellow"],"answerLetter":"C"},
// {"id":1210,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Consider the following set-ups: (缺少圖片，文件名: image[[104, 483, 464, 728]] and image[[587, 483, 919, 727]]) Which hook would corrode first?","points":5,"options":["iron hook (1)","iron hook (2)","copper hook (3)","copper hook (4)"],"answerLetter":"B"},
// {"id":1211,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Consider the following information concerning metals W, X, Y and Z: (1) Heating oxide of W gives metal W. (2) Heating metal X in steam gives a colourless gas. (3) Putting metal Y in CH3CO2H(aq) gives a colourless gas. (4) Putting metal Z in CuSO4(aq) gives a reddish-brown solid. Which of these metals has the lowest reactivity?","points":5,"options":["W","X","Y","Z"],"answerLetter":"A"},
// {"id":1212,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Which of the following observations would be expected when some calcium granules are put in cold water inside a test tube? (1) A cloudy mixture is formed. (2) The test tube becomes warm. (3) Colourless gas bubbles are formed.","points":5,"options":["(1) and (2) only","(1) and (3) only","(2) and (3) only","(1), (2) and (3)"],"answerLetter":"D"},
// {"id":1213,"subject":"化學","topic":"3. Metals","type":"choice","text":"Consider the following experimental set-up: (缺少圖片，文件名: image[[155, 627, 846, 732]]) Which of the following would NOT be X?","points":5,"options":["iron","zinc","copper","magnesium"],"answerLetter":"C"},
