// {"id":1228,"subject":"化學","topic":"5+11. Fossil Fuels, Carbon Compounds and Chemistry of Carbon Compounds","type":"choice","text":"Hydrogen, methane and butane are commonly used fuels. Which of the following statements is correct?","points":5,"options":["Hydrogen is a more environmental friendly fuel than butane.","Methane burns with a more sooty flame than butane.","Hydrogen, methane and butane all belong to the same homologous series.","On complete combustion, one mole of methane releases more carbon dioxide than one mole of butane."],"answerLetter":"A"},
